page.title: 09LAND COVER,LICKEY/CATSHILL
page.content: In our area,landscape plays a very important part in our lives.The main features are hills, fields,woodland and four villages dotted around.There are three schools in the area. In the whole area there are ten farms. There is an active quarry.Many houses have large gardens. {Buildings} The oldest house in our area was built in 1648 and is called THE CLOCK HOUSE.It is timber_framed infilled with brick. Some houses, including Lickey Grange, were built by Lord Austin. A few nailmakers' cottages still stand. { {Ecology In our area we have found there are more Beech and Oak trees than any other species of trees.A couple of Silver Birches have been sent from America as presents.
